						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 49: 1118-19 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 24 sheep for two <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamps by Taṇḍuṟai uḍaiyāṉ Malai Nambaṉ to god Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiya Mahādēva in Śōḻakulas vallinallūr in Paṭṭāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
